properties.Title: Blowing Snow Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Poor visibility in snow and blowing snow is expected or occurring in some locations. Total snowfall: 5 to 10 cm. Maximum wind gusts: 70 km/h. Locations: Labrador Straits area. Time span: Monday morning until Monday evening. Remarks: Fresh snowfall will combine with strengthening northeasterly winds Monday morning to produce poor visibility in blowing snow, especially inland over the Trans-Labrador Highway. Snow is expected to taper off Monday evening, ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Blowing snow advisories are issued when winds are expected to create blowing snow giving poor visibility to 800 metres or less for at least 3 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.

properties.Title: Freezing Drizzle Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Areas of freezing drizzle are expected or occurring. Freezing drizzle is expected tonight. Location: northern New Brunswick. Timing: until overnight tonight. Remarks: Freezing drizzle mixed with drizzle and flurries will change to periods of snow near midnight or overnight tonight. ### Surfaces such as highways, roads, walkways and parking lots may become icy and slippery. Freezing drizzle advisories are issued when drizzle falling in sub-zero temperatures is expected to freeze on contact, and over time create icy surfaces. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NBstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NBStorm.
